channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Our Stubborn Media Loses Even More Credibility in Addressing the Military Service of the VP Candidates
9/11 conspirators' future plea deals in jeopardy as NY House Republicans move to block them
item.description: House Republicans from New York are moving to block the Pentagon from being able to strike a plea deal to avoid the death penalty for the accused plotters of Sept. 11.

item.title: Biden Backs Trump in Eliminating Taxes on Tips
item.description: President Joe Biden supports the idea of eliminating taxes on tips for service and hospitality workers, an idea first proposed by former President Donald Trump, the White House said Monday..

item.title: Trump Throws a Curveball With Revamped Social Media Game, Takes Completely New Tone
Shop owner reveals heart-wrenching experience after BLM riots 'destroyed' his store on Gov Walz's watch
item.description: Fox News Digital spoke with an immigrant business owner in St. Paul, Minnesota, about the 2020 George Floyd riot that destroyed his business and took him years to recover from.

item.title: Pro-Trump Super PAC Dropping $100 Million on TV Ads
item.description: A pro-Trump super PAC said it plans to spend $100 million in TV ads leading up to Labor Day.

item.title: REPORT: US Offering Maduro and His Henchmen Amnesty If He Cedes Power
Dems hitting Vance with debunked vulgar claim 'undermine' their anti-Trump credibility, strategist says
item.description: Democrats have continued to jokingly allude to a rumor about former President Trump's running mate, Ohio Sen. JD Vance, despite the story being debunked.

item.title: Sen. Graham: Ukraine Foray Into Russia Bold, Beautiful
item.description: Sen. Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., called Ukraine's shock cross-border operation into Russia's Kursk region "brilliant" and "bold" in a visit to Kyiv on Monday, and he urged the Biden administration to provide Ukraine with the weapons it needs.

item.title: SPOILER: Jill Stein to Pick 'Palestinian-American' VP Candidate
Trump claims 'nobody' cheered Harris outside Air Force Two despite video, images of crowds
item.description: Former President Trump is claiming there was "nobody" waiting for Kamala Harris to arrive at a rally in Detroit last week, but video and images tell a different story.

item.title: US Says it Expects Gaza Peace Talks to Continue, Cease-Fire Possible
item.description: The U.S. expects Gaza peace talks to move forward as planned, the State Department said on Monday, adding it believes a cease-fire deal remains possible even after Hamas cast doubt on whether it would participate in a Thursday meeting called by mediators.

item.title: Damning: DHS Whistleblowers Faced Retaliation After Exposing Agency's Failure to Comply With DNA Law
Former leader of Walz's battalion publishes scathing message aimed at governor's military career: Report
item.description: The battalion commander of Minnesota Gov. Tim Walzâ€™s former Army National Guard unit slammed Vice President Kamala Harris' running mate for claiming a command sergeant major rank.

item.title: Mitch McConnell: Dems' Complete Control 'Our Worst Nightmare'
item.description: Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell, R-Ky., told Republican lawmakers in Kentucky that Democrats winning all three branches of government in November's general election would be "our worst nightmare."
